tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All results are within normal limits except for a mildly elevated HbA1c (5.8%), which suggests prediabetes or impaired glucose tolerance. Glucose is currently normal. Recommend clinical correlation, lifestyle counseling, and repeat HbA1c monitoring. No evidence of renal or electrolyte abnormalities.
